ative diseases by preventing the disruption of neural functioning. How? Because together they fight amyloids from building.\r\n9. EDTA (calcium disodium edetate). Strong heavy metal chelator. Also, strong antihypercalcemia and anticoagulation properties. Actually removes/reduces calcific plaque in arteries.\r\n\r\n ", "author": "NecturusMaculosus", "created": 1777674413016, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Skogin", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Concrete things you can take to prevent and heal covid vaccine damage.", "last_comment_created": 1777675923028, "content": "<ol>\n<li>NAC and bromelain together make spike proteins &quot;unwind&quot; so they no longer function (spike proteins are responsible for the fibrinogen clots found throughout the body  accelerating death in humans)</li>\n<li>Black seed (nigella sativa)appears to keep spike proteins from bonding with ACE2 receptors by binding first with ACE2 receptors</li>\n<li>Glutathione supplements help body purge graphene oxide. Two brazil nuts a day provide adequate selenium to allow glutathione to work properly</li>\n<li>Dimethylglycine (DMG)supplements help purge graphene oxide</li>\n<li>Resveratrol &quot;destroys graphene oxide ability to cause harmful oxidation &quot;</li>\n<li>Chlorine dioxide as a treatment for autoimmune diseases</li>\n<li>Nattokinase (works by dissolving blood clots, increasing blood flow, and reducing blood pressure)</li>\n<li>Serrapeptase (serrapeptase dissolves both clots and atherosclerotic plaques. It removes fatty deposits, cholesterol, and cellular waste products inside arteries. When used orally with nattokinase, serrapeptase can protect against neurodegenerative diseases by preventing the disruption of neural functioning. How? Because together they fight amyloids from building.</li>\n<li>EDTA (calcium disodium edetate). Strong heavy metal chelator. Also, strong antihypercalcemia and anticoagulation properties. Actually removes/reduces calcific plaque in arteries.</li>\n</ol>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 28, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}